Has the same problem, we can&#x27;t support the syntax:<p><pre><code>  let integer: i32 = some_integer_array.at(i);
  let reference: &i32 = &some_integer_array.at(i);
</code></pre>
with the desired semantics, without introducing new language concepts.<p>In any case, we did use methods for indexing vectors for a while and it was quite annoying; the shorter syntax is nice.
